   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="languagestudies1">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>105</x>
      <y>180</y>
      <width>421</width>
      <height>531</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }

</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; line-height:138%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;While in Europe, José Rizal mastered multiple languages, including Spanish, French, German, and Italian, enhancing his access to progressive literature and ideas. Influenced by thinkers like &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Voltaire&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Rousseau&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Schiller&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Kant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, he expanded his intellectual horizons and strengthened his advocacy for reform. His linguistic skills also connected him with fellow reform-minded Filipinos and facilitated his writing of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Noli Me Tangere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;El Filibusterismo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; in Spanish.      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; line-height:138%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; line-height:138%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;In 1885, Rizal earned his medical degree from the Universidad Central de Madrid and a Bachelor of Arts in Philosophy and Letters. Specializing in ophthalmology, he gained recognition as an eye doctor, driven by his goal to treat his mother’s eye condition. Further training in Paris and Germany solidified his reputation as a skilled physician.        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
    </property>
   </widget>
